&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Senior Vice President, Marketing&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: &lt;/strong&gt;Marketing&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the Leadership Team, the SVP of Marketing will shape company strategy and lead a fully integrated Marketing &amp;amp; Communications organization. Reporting to the President (and partnering closely with the CEO and CRO), this leader will own the end-to-end marketing engine that drives predictable growth—pipeline creation, product and category positioning, and customer lifecycle programs that improve adoption, retention, and expansion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scale a mission-driven marketing function at a $100M ARR health technology SaaS company at a pivotal growth stage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a more predictable pipeline engine (efficiency, conversion, and forecasting rigor).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strengthen category narrative and trust in a complex healthcare buying environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deepen lifecycle marketing to improve adoption and retention and expand customer advocacy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1) Marketing strategy and operating system&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and lead the marketing strategy aligned to company growth goals (pipeline, ARR, retention/NRR).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own marketing planning, budgeting, scorecards, and executive reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish operating rhythms with Sales, Product, and Customer Success (SLAs, pipeline reviews, launch readiness).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2) Demand generation &amp;amp; pipeline acceleration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and optimize multi-channel demand programs (ABM, performance, field/events, partners, content).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Revenue Operations to improve lead flow, scoring, routing, and attribution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own marketing-sourced pipeline targets and ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3) Positioning, brand, and communications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define a compelling, differentiated narrative that builds trust and credibility in the market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and lead an integrated messaging strategy across web, content, campaigns, sales assets, and executive communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead PR/comms strategy, thought leadership, and analyst relations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead a structured internal communications strategy that drives alignment, transparency, and engagement across cross-functional teams, reinforcing company vision and strategic priorities in partnership with executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4) Product marketing &amp;amp; go-to-market readiness&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own buyer personas, positioning, packaging/offer strategy (in partnership with Product/Revenue leaders), and launch orchestration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate product capabilities into clear value propositions and enablement for Sales and CS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish competitive intelligence and messaging discipline across segments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5) Customer marketing &amp;amp; lifecycle&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build lifecycle programs that improve onboarding, product adoption, renewal readiness, and advocacy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Customer Success on retention drivers and churn reduction initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scale customer proof: case studies, references, CABs, community, referrals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
